  "description": "Bounded promotion proof for wchar_abi C23 wide aliases, char16 conversion, wide memory-stream, and wide-string duplication entrypoints whose implementation is native Rust ABI adaptation with expected libio, codec, errno, and allocator bridge reachability.",
  "rationale": "The C23 __isoc23_* rows forward into FrankenLibC wide scanf and wide integer conversion implementations. The mbrtoc16 row is a char16 adapter over the native char32/wchar conversion path. The open_wmemstream and wcsdup rows allocate through FrankenLibC allocation and stream registries. Host-delegation census hits are bootstrap, errno, libio-registry, codec, and allocator bridge symbols, not direct semantic call-through for the promoted wchar API bodies.",
